When I watch a video like this one, I'm really questioning reality. I also use AI. To code, to brain storm, to write texts, ... And it always messes up. Even with a lot of context, it still consistently messes up.

I'm debating frequently, if I should just refer back to the documentation of whatever I'm working on or if I should let the AI rip. And letting AI rip has rarely been a good experience. If I let it do stuff mindlessly, it somehow always fucks up. It chases itself in circular patterns but it never gets a "new" idea so to speak. And then it needs me, the human, to have a good look at what it's suggesting and going - huh, maybe let me just try something rather obvious that the LLM walked past like two times already - and the more often than not, my idea fixes the problem, not AI.

So when I hear people ranting and raving about AI being so good and such a good companion, I'm keep wondering whether I'm living in the same reality as you. My best example was a piece of code I asked AI to write. 10 lines. It confused two variables (which it named mind you, it wasn't my code that it was supposed to integrate with) which lead to O(n^2) memory consumption instead of O(n). And thus a small problem crashed my computer because of memory overflow. Ten bloody lines of code and it couldn't even handle this. So considering this I'm very apprehensive to just letting an agent loose on my code and even on my hard drive.
